Below is an example of a simple web app contained entirely within a single HTML file, with embedded CSS and JavaScript. This sample creates a visual representation of a recursive "creator" concept, where the user can click to reveal additional "creators" down the chain.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Recursive Creator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .creator {
            margin: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 2px solid #007BFF;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #fff;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        .creator:hover {
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="creator-0" class="creator">Creator 0</div>

<script>
    let creatorCount = 0;

    function createNewCreator(parentId) {
        creatorCount++;
        const newDiv = document.createElement('div');
        newDiv.id = 'creator-' + creatorCount;
        newDiv.className = 'creator';
        newDiv.innerText = 'Creator ' + creatorCount;
        newDiv.onclick = () => createNewCreator(newDiv.id);
        newDiv.style.marginLeft = '20px'; // Indent child creators

        // Append the new creator to the parent div
        const parentDiv = document.getElementById(parentId);
        parentDiv.appendChild(newDiv);
    }

    document.getElementById('creator-0').onclick = function() {
        createNewCreator(this.id);
    };
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The body contains a single initial div representing the first creator (`Creator 0`). 
- **CSS**: Styles for the body, the creator divs, and hover effects are specified to create a visually appealing interface.
- **JavaScript**: A script that manages the creation of new creator divs when any existing creator is clicked. Each new creator is indented to show hierarchy visually.

### Usage:
1. Create a new file (e.g., `creator.html`).
2. Copy and paste the above code into the file.
3. Open the file in a web browser to see the web app in action. Each click on any "creator" will add a new child "creator" to the display.
